.</span><hr size=1> This is one of the least used yet most valuable of commands to use if you play a pet class. Using the command will return a percentage value of your pet’s health, or a notice that you do not have a pet. It is best used when you solo and want to meditate during battles.<br>
<br>
Engage the mob, send in your pet, and hit it with a few spells. If you are a necromancer or enchanter you may want to cast fear just before meditating. Keep the mob you are fighting selected before you start to meditate. While you are sitting you can see the health bar of the mob. Use the /pet report health command to get a percentage of your pet’s health.<br>
<br>
Things to note:<br>
<br>
If you are a necromancer using reverse kiting, a decline in health as reported by your pet will let you know that the pet is taking damage. This means that either the fear wore off, or you picked up another mob to deal with.<br>
<br>
Enchanters cannot use this command on their pets, but it is very handy with charmed MOB’s. If the report comes bas as “you do not have a pet” then either the charmed MOB is dead, or the charm broke. This was extremely handy back before Verant added the text lines notifying you when spells wear off.<br>
<br>
When grouped with other pet users, pet report health will warn you when you need to use the command to turn off taunting. Again, enchanters cannot turn of taunt on their summoned pets. <p><P><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Reog</FONT></B> the educated ogre of <A HREF="http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com"><IMG SRC = "http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com/files/mcsmall.gif" WIDTH=195 HEIGHT=32  BORDER=0></A></P>
